Diagnosis. Head dark brown dorsally (
Figs 12–13
). Anterior angles of pronotum each with a stout, spine-like tubercle, surpassing lateral margins of each compound eye; anterolateral margins each with 1–2 small tubercles; each humeral angle bilobed apically, anterior lobe with 2–3 processes; posterior margin weakly concave (
Figs 1–3
). Apex of hemelytral radial vein calloused; corium ivory, reaching anterior margin of abdominal segment VI; membrane reaching anterior margin of abdominal segment VIII on females (
Fig. 15
) and surpassing abdominal apex on males (
Fig. 14
). Male genitalia: posterolateral angles of pygophore rounded; inferior layer of ventral rim weakly emarginate, with a bilobed projection medially; parameres acute apically (
Figs 18–24
). Female genitalia: posterior margin of each gonocoxite 8 rectilinear; posterior margin of each laterotergite 8 acute; laterotergites 9 digitiform (
Figs 32–35
).

